body:
Hey Alex. We couldn't get the makeshift sensor to work reliably last night...

And sorry, I accidentally packed the ESP32 board with me. Do you need it? I could drop it off at The Cannon for you, but I can't stay long.
I'll try to be there around 10:30am to drop it off for you.
What is your email so that you can be credited for being part of the group?

hnguyen913@gmail.com

How was the rest of the hackathon?

It was good. We didn't win, but it was a good experience. I am planning on doing it next year.
Also, how am I supposed to set up react native?

I'm glad you had a good experience! I definitely think this is a worthwhile project and Houston needs a city-wide mesh network of weather sensors. 

For React Native, there may be a bit of a learning curve, but it's good that you already know Javascript. Try to read through this documentation and see if you can set up Expo with Android. Let me know if you have any questions.

[https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/getting-started.html](https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/getting-started.html)

This tool may also be helpful with getting started: [https://snack.expo.io/](https://snack.expo.io/)
http://rainsensors.com/rain-gauge-modes/
Hieu, what did we use on AWS to make the web server, I am going to try to make my own so that I can access it.

I used [AWS IoT](https://aws.amazon.com/iot/). Were you able to get a student account?

See if you can follow the tutorial to get started. You'll need to set up your own pub/sub instance with your own security certificates.
https://exploreembedded.com/wiki/Secure_IOT_with_AWS_and_Hornbill_ESP32

I was unable because it wasn't working. I am trying to integrate the server into React Native. I don't know how to integrate AWS into React Native. 
I would really appreciate your help.

Were you able to get started with React Native? Do you have a barebones app running on Android?

I haven't used React Native with AWS yet, but it looks like you can use the [Amplify Framework](https://aws-amplify.github.io/docs/js/tutorials/building-react-native-apps/) to connect it to AWS IoT and retrieve sensor data over the PubSub interface.
https://aws-amplify.github.io/docs/js/pubsub
Did you use the MQTT.fx tool for the setup?

I am so lost right now! I don't know how to set up AWS. 
I have gotten React Native to run on IOS already!

My visual studio code refuses to run, at this point, I don't even know what to do. Here are the keys and such so you can help me. Let me know if you need anything else for this. Send me the files with the altered formatting. I already have AWS.iot stuff for the ESP32, so if I need to change that, I can. I have been unable to find the format guidelines. Maybe we could chat and share screens or something so that you can walk me through how to do all of this stuff. It would allow me to do it without needing your help.

Here is the last part of the stuff you need:
Thing(Topic) name is: "Test_1A"
Host Address: a7vdwzgtgavmo-ats.iot.us-east-2.amazonaws.com
I think the server name is the same as the topic name if it is not let me know.

Hieu, in order to use Amplify I have to have Expo.cli. At the moment, I am unable to run that entirely. I can't even use npm install on the app! I have been stuck using snack.expo.io for the past week and a half.
If you need my Expo account stuffs or the AWS account stuffs, let me know.

Alex, maybe we can meet sometime this weekend to get you set up with the CLI. Either at The Cannon or we can work remotely. Do you have a Mac computer? I've found that React Native works best on Macs and it's also needed to develop iOS apps.
This weekend I am studying for finals. Next weekend will work. No I do not have a Mac.
Ok, keep me updated. Good luck with finals!
Thanks!
Does tomorrow work?
I can probably do late afternoon tomorrow, like around 4pm or later. Meet at The Cannon?

I figured out the name for the app
Puddl- Dryve wherever, whenever

We could meet up tomorrow at the Cannon.
Around 3:00.

Sorry, I won't be able to meet today to work on this. Maybe later this week or another weekend?

How is your progress coming along? Are you still stuck on some parts?
My progress is still at a halt due to an inability to get React Native to work the way I want it to. I want it to run on Local Host but it doesn’t want to work.
Hi Hieu, can we chat? My number is+18322622074. Call me to chat about the app.
Hmm, I'm not sure what you mean by "run on Local Host." It might be easier to meet in person to work through some of these issues.
Hey! Thought you might be interested in this event: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/houston-social-good-hackathon-tickets-77033955635
